    <item>
      <title>Re: Vah Shir cloak quests</title>
      <link>http://eqforums.station.sony.com/eq/board/message?board.id=Quests&amp;message.id=774#M774</link>
      <description>&lt;DIV&gt;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I have the cloak on five different Vah Shir characters.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;I can confirm the owlbear tendons were dropping about a month ago but I don't hunt there often any more unless someone is willing to pay for me to make them a part for the quest.&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp; It's been months since I hunted the Sonics to any extent so I can't confirm that they still drop but there is no reason they wouldn't except for a bug.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The tendons (or almost any of the quest parts) drop only in Hollowshade Moor and can drop during the war.&amp;nbsp; They are uncommon but I would not say they are rare.&amp;nbsp; They are most likely to drop from the outdoor wanderers in that species's home area but can rarely drop from any appropriate MoB.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;Owlbear tendons are particularly difficult since the revamp as there are very few outside wanderers now and they don't stay in any one spot for long.&amp;nbsp; If you really need the tendons&amp;nbsp;try putting the owlbears on the Islands and the farming the patrolling owlbears there.&amp;nbsp; The drop rate isn't great but it's better than farming two wanderers for days on end.&amp;nbsp; &lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;To put the owlbears on the islands you have to kill the Grimling Cheiftain and the then the five Grimling Defenders that will spawn in front of the Chieftain's hut.&amp;nbsp; In a few minutes some owlbears will come and take over that area.&amp;nbsp; If you are below level 50 this may be difficult and require help.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;The Sonic wolf Tendons are a little easier as there are 4 wanderers that have a good chance of dropping them.&amp;nbsp; Two of them are near the Grimling Forest zone line, another spwans in the area between the rivers near where the rivers part.&amp;nbsp; The fourth&amp;nbsp;spawns between the Sonic wolf cave and the Grimling Islands.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
&lt;DIV&gt;This quest is long, frustrating and painful but if you keep at it you will finish it eventually.&amp;nbsp; The cloak is very nice for the level you can get it at and my Shaman still proudly wears his at level 61.&lt;/DIV&gt;&#xD;
